14 SECTION 1.
15 Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to motor vehicles and traffic, is
16 amended in Code Section 40-1-1, relating to definitions, by revising paragraph (27.1) and
17 adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
18 "(27.1) 'Miniature on-road vehicle' means any motorized vehicle designed and
19 manufactured for use upon roadways in another country that has been imported into the
20 United States with a valid certificate of title or registration from the exporting country
21 and in compliance with all federal importation requirements and which has the following
22 characteristics:
23 (A) Has the capability to transport persons;
24 (B) Operates between 25 miles per hour (40.2 kilometers per hour) and 65 miles per
25 hour (104.6 kilometers per hour);
26 (C) Has an overall width of 80 inches (2,030 millimeters) or less, exclusive of
27 accessories or attachments;
28 (D) Is designed to travel on four or more wheels;
29 (E) Uses a steering wheel for steering control;
30 (F) Contains a nonstraddle seat;
31 (G) Has a gross vehicle weight rating of less than 4,000 pounds (1,814 kilograms); and
32 (H) Is not designed or manufactured as a golf cart, all-terrain vehicle, or multipurpose
33 off-highway vehicle.
34 (27.2) 'Minimal risk condition' means a low-risk operating mode in which a fully
35 autonomous vehicle operating without a human driver achieves a reasonably safe state,
36 such as bringing the vehicle to a complete stop, upon experiencing a failure of the
37 vehicle's automated driving system that renders the vehicle unable to perform the entire
38 dynamic driving task."
